{
  "question_text": "<h3>Longest String Chain</h3><p>Find the length of the longest possible word chain where each word is a predecessor of the next (successor has one more character than predecessor).</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "List of words.",
  "output_format": "Int.",
  "constraints": [
    "words.length <= 1000",
    "word.length <= 16"
  ],
  "explanation": "Sort words by length. For each word, generate all possible predecessors by removing one character and look them up in a DP map. `dp[word] = max(dp[prev]) + 1`. The answer is the maximum value in `dp`.",
  "answer": "def longestStrChain(words):\n    dp = {}\n    for w in sorted(words, key=len):\n        dp[w] = 1\n        for i in range(len(w)):\n            prev = w[:i] + w[i+1:]\n            if prev in dp: dp[w] = max(dp[w], dp[prev] + 1)\n    return max(dp.values())",
  "boilerplate": {
